# Project Summary

RaceCAN Digital Kit is a software simulated low voltage telemetry system designed for motorsports, robotics, and Formula SAE style learning.

The project models how a sensor node reads vehicle style signals, detects warnings and faults, packages data into CAN style messages, displays telemetry on a dashboard, and logs data to CSV.

## What Was Built

Week 1 produced a working software demo with:

1. Python telemetry simulator
2. CAN style message encoder
3. Fault detection logic
4. Terminal dashboard
5. CSV logger
6. Command line interface
7. Product focused documentation

## Simulated Signals

RaceCAN V1 simulates:

1. Battery voltage
2. Temperature
3. Throttle position
4. Brake position
5. Current draw
6. External fault state
7. Heartbeat status

## Faults and Warnings

RaceCAN V1 detects:

1. Voltage warning
2. Undervoltage fault
3. Temperature warning
4. Overtemperature fault
5. Current warning
6. Overcurrent fault
7. Sensor range fault
8. External fault
9. Communication fault placeholder

## CAN Style Messages

RaceCAN V1 uses these message IDs:

| CAN ID | Message Name |
|---|---|
| 0x100 | Heartbeat |
| 0x101 | Voltage Status |
| 0x102 | Temperature Status |
| 0x103 | Driver Inputs |
| 0x104 | Current Status |
| 0x105 | Fault Status |

